    "description": "We at NSE are looking for an experienced Risk Analyst based out of Amritsar. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout NSE:\nNSE is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n• Develop financial models and projections for business planning\n• Maintain general ledger and ensure accurate bookkeeping\n• Prepare annual reports and investor presentations\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBBS / MD / MS from recognized medical college\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in Credit Analysis\n• Proficiency in Python for Finance\n• Proficiency in Financial Reporting\n• Proficiency in QuickBooks\n• Proficiency in IFRS\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Amritsar, Punjab, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with NSE!",
